table_trans: This ad-hoc promotion is in the public interest as an administrative urgency to the posts lying vacant due to the deputation of officers of the Deputy Secretary cadre in the Ministry of Home Affairs in a very temporary manner.
This ad-hoc promotion will not entitle the officers concerned to any rights of regular promotion.
The ad-hoc promotion shall be for a period of 11 months from the date of joining or the order of promotion of the officer / employee who has left on deputation, whichever is earlier.

These ad-hoc promotions are being made subject to the demotion of the minimum officer in this order, if a vacancy in the Deputy Secretary cadre is not available to the senior officers / staff on deputation in the Deputy Secretary cadre on their repatriation.
The ad-hoc promotion is being made subject to the final decision of the Special Leave Petition No. ID1 filed in the Supreme Court.

This ad-hoc promotion is being made subject to the final decision of the High Court, Bombay in the pending Writ Petitions K र.3310/2021 and K र.3311/2021 आय.ए.क, K र.1854/2021 and K 1855/2021 as well as in the Writ Petition K र.3312/2021.
The ad-hoc promotion is being made subject to the final decision in the pending original Application No. ID1 (Mr. Kiran Jadhav et al.) at the Maharashtra Administrative Tribunal, Mumbai.

This ad-hoc promotion is being made subject to the final decision to be taken in the pending Application No. 1066/19 (Mr. Ulhas Shankar Bhote et al.) at the Maharashtra Administrative Tribunal, Mumbai.
